spanGrp.span: There are forty families left in our village.
bizım köv nä šindi ğaldi ğırh äv
People all have left to Russia and to Greece.
halh getti urusetä gretsiaya äp dağildi
Only old people like me and a few young people stayed in this village.
burdada ğaldi vasnavnom bänımkimın ğoja adamlar biräz jaallarda šei ettılar
People from Ajaria came here for living.
gäldılär bizım kövä ajariadan onnarda yaširlär
We will get used to it and life will be better.
nu vseravno paka priviknim olur yašamah ničego epeim
My neighbours that have come from Ajaria are very good and we have friendship.
družbamız var o adamlarınanda an bänım ğonšularım var ey ğonšidıllar ajariadan gälmıšlär
I can’t say anything bad about it.
I don’t know how our youth will be but we are old enough age, I will be already eighty years old.
bizdä näblem jaalarımız näsıl olur näsıl olmaz bizımdä uže vädämız tamam uže skoro säksän yašında oliram
bizım mı khristiani khristiani u nas narod
We go to the church and they go to the mosque in nearby village Kumbat.
v tserkov idut ani idut v mečet v sasednem sele kumbati est mečet ani tuda idut
If someone from their families dies they take them to bury to Ajaria.
u nikh esli ktota umiraet hä onnarın adam ki ölirsä oni götürirlär ajariaya burda gömmirlär hä
I don’t know how they bury.
bülmirım daa näsıl gömir näsıl gömmirlär
We do it by Christian traditions.
